The paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on modeling future observations and rewards, which falls under the category of predictive modeling. The paper also discusses the computational challenges of modeling high-dimensional observations, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also deals with planning and decision-making, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
